LOCUS       CBP_tag                   26 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  26-aa calmodulin-binding peptide (CBP) from the C-terminus of rabbit
            skeletal/cardiac myosin light-chain kinase; binds calmodulin
            Ca2+-dependently (nanomolar Kd), purified on calmodulin resin and
            eluted with EGTA; the C-terminal affinity handle of the TAP /
            InterPlay tandem-affinity systems..
